DESCRIPTION end
|\fBarki-sort\fP reads metadata from a file or standard input, sorts them
|as requested and outputs them to standard output.

OPTIONS end
|.SH EXAMPLES
|Here are some example invocations of \fBarki-sort\fP:
|.P
|.nf
|  # Output the grib messages sorted by origin first, then by
|  # reverse timerange order, then by reference time
|  arki-sort --order=origin,-timerange,reftime file.grib > sorted.grib
|.fi
|
|.SH SEE ALSO
|.BR arki-scan (1)
